      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUCY LULU (2) raced on the pace last start before fading to finish seventh, beaten 4 lengths, over 1400m at Narrandera. Draws the inside alley and is sure to prove tough to rein in. TOP ACT (3) finished out of the money two starts back then was beaten only 1.5 lengths when fifth over 1600m at Coonabarabran three-and-a-half weeks ago after being in contention on the turn. Suitably placed so anticipating a better run this time. The well-related THE TYLER (4) (half to G3 winner and G2 placed Col 'N' Lil) just missed the frame last start when fourth over 1200m at this track. Must raise the bar but this looks well within his grasp. WOLF POINT (7) ran a nice race last time out over 1350m at Julia Creek, finishing second and beaten 0.8 lengths. Best figures measure up and is set to run well again.",
